  "day04.txt": "DAY 4 – PERSONAL CLEANSING\r\n\r\nPrayer Assignment – Cleansing Myself Before God\r\n\r\nToday, come before the Lord with humility and allow the Holy Spirit to search every area of your life. Do not justify sin or hide weaknesses. Bring everything into God's light so He can cleanse, restore, and transform you.\r\n\r\n1. Pray for Your Thoughts\r\n\r\nAsk God to renew your mind and remove every ungodly thought. Pray against:\r\n\r\nFear, anxiety, worry and unbelief\r\n\r\nPride, self-exaltation and self-reliance\r\n\r\nLust, impurity and fantasy\r\n\r\nBitterness, offense and judgment\r\n\r\nNegative mindsets and strongholds\r\n\r\n\r\nDeclare: \"Lord, I take every thought captive to the obedience of Christ. Renew my mind and fill it with Your truth.\" (2 Corinthians 10:5)\r\n\r\n2. Pray for Your Words\r\n\r\nRepent for every careless word you have spoken. Ask God to cleanse your mouth from:\r\n\r\nComplaining and murmuring\r\n\r\nGossip and slander\r\n\r\nHarsh, hurtful or angry speech\r\n\r\nLies, exaggeration and manipulation\r\n\r\nWords that brought death instead of life\r\n\r\n\r\nDeclare: \"Holy Spirit, place a guard over my mouth. Let my words bring life, truth and encouragement.\" (Proverbs 18:21)\r\n\r\n3. Pray for Your Heart\r\n\r\nInvite Jesus to search your heart completely. Repent of:\r\n\r\nUnforgiveness and bitterness\r\n\r\nJealousy and envy\r\n\r\nHidden sin and compromise\r\n\r\nAnger, resentment and rebellion\r\n\r\nWrong desires and selfish ambitions\r\n\r\n\r\nDeclare: \"Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a steadfast spirit within me.\" (Psalm 51:10)\r\n\r\n4. Pray for Pure Motives\r\n\r\nAsk God to purify every motive behind your actions. Repent of:\r\n\r\nSeeking people's approval\r\n\r\nPride and selfish ambition\r\n\r\nHidden agendas\r\n\r\nSelf-will instead of God's will\r\n\r\n\r\nDeclare: \"Father, let everything I do be for Your glory alone.\" (1 Samuel 16:7)\r\n\r\n5. Pray Over Your Lifestyle\r\n\r\nSurrender your daily life to Christ. Repent of:\r\n\r\nSinful habits and addictions\r\n\r\nSpiritual laziness\r\n\r\nWasting time\r\n\r\nCompromise with the world\r\n\r\nWrong priorities\r\n\r\n\r\nAsk the Holy Spirit to establish a lifestyle of holiness and obedience.\r\n\r\nToday's Action\r\n\r\nSpend time in honest self-examination.\r\n\r\nConfess every known sin.\r\n\r\nForgive everyone who has hurt you.\r\n\r\nFast from something that controls your flesh.\r\n\r\nAsk the Holy Spirit to cleanse and fill every area of your life.\r\n",
