  "day07.txt": "✝️ DAY 7 – FASTING\r\n\r\nTHE CROSS\r\n\r\nMORE THAN A SYMBOL —\r\n\r\nOUR VICTORY SIGN ON THE WAY TO HEAVEN\r\n\r\nSuffering. Death. Redemption. Victory. Life. Lordship.\r\n\r\n> “It is finished!”\r\n\r\nJohn 19:30\r\n---\r\n\r\n❓ WHY ARE WE FASTING TODAY?\r\n\r\nWe fast today to focus our hearts on Jesus and the Cross.\r\n\r\nTo understand what He has done for us and to allow the power of the Cross to transform our lives\r\n---\r\n\r\n✝️ THE CROSS TELLS THE STORY\r\n\r\n❤️ GOD'S LOVE\r\n\r\nGod so loved the world that He gave His Son.\r\nJohn 3:16\r\n\r\n🩸 OUR PRICE WAS PAID\r\n\r\nJesus carried our guilt and paid our debt with His blood.\r\n1 Peter 2:24\r\n\r\n🔗 OUR FREEDOM\r\n\r\nThe Cross broke the power of sin, death, and darkness.\r\nColossians 2:13–15\r\n\r\n👑 OUR VICTORY\r\n\r\nAt the Cross, Jesus defeated the enemy and secured the victory.\r\nColossians 2:15\r\n\r\n➡️ OUR WAY TO THE FATHER\r\n\r\nThe Cross opened the way to the Father—today and forever.\r\nHebrews 10:19–22\r\n---\r\n\r\n✝️ THE CROSS — THE CENTER OF EVERYTHING\r\n\r\nEverything revolves around Jesus.\r\n\r\n👑 SUFFERING\r\nHe suffered for us.\r\nIsaiah 53:5\r\n\r\n🩸 BLOOD\r\nThe blood of Jesus brings cleansing, freedom, and life.\r\nLeviticus 17:11\r\n\r\n⚰️ DEATH\r\nJesus died so that our old life could die.\r\nRomans 6:6\r\n\r\n🌅 RESURRECTION\r\nHe did not remain in the grave—He is alive!\r\n1 Corinthians 15:3–4\r\n\r\n🕊️ FORGIVENESS\r\nThrough His wounds we are healed and forgiven.\r\nIsaiah 53:5\r\n\r\n👑 LORDSHIP\r\nJesus has all authority in heaven and on earth.\r\nMatthew 28:18\r\n\r\n> The Cross is God's love in action.\r\n\r\nIt is our freedom, our healing, our hope, and our eternal life.\r\n---\r\n\r\n✅ WHAT DID THE CROSS ACCOMPLISH?\r\n\r\n1. Forgiveness and reconciliation.\r\n\r\n2. The power of sin was broken.\r\n\r\n3. Satan was defeated.\r\n\r\n4. We were adopted as children of God.\r\n\r\n5. Healing and restoration became available.\r\n\r\n6. Access to the Father was opened.\r\n\r\n7. Redemption and freedom were secured.\r\n\r\n8. Righteousness and holiness were given.\r\n\r\n9. The Holy Spirit was poured out.\r\n\r\n10. Eternal life became our inheritance.\r\n---\r\n\r\n✝️ THE CROSS IN MY LIFE — IT WORKS!\r\n\r\n⚔️ MY WEAPON\r\n\r\nI fight through the power of the Cross.\r\n\r\nIt disarms the enemy.\r\n\r\nIt breaks chains.\r\n\r\nIt destroys strongholds.\r\n\r\nIt overcomes darkness.\r\n\r\nEphesians 6:12\r\n---\r\n\r\n👑 MY KINGDOM\r\n\r\nThe Kingdom of God rules in me.\r\n\r\nChrist is King.\r\n\r\nGod's will becomes my desire.\r\n\r\nHis authority governs my life.\r\nLuke 17:21\r\n---\r\n\r\n🛤️ MY WAY\r\n\r\nThe Cross leads me to the Father.\r\n\r\nIt opens the way to heaven.\r\n\r\nIt leads me into truth.\r\n\r\nIt guides me in discipleship.\r\nJohn 14:6\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n❤️ MY LIFE\r\n\r\nThe life of Jesus lives in me.\r\n\r\nI die to self.\r\n\r\nChrist lives through me.\r\n\r\nI become a new creation.\r\nGalatians 2:20\r\n---\r\n\r\n🙏 PRAYER ASSIGNMENT FOR TODAY\r\n\r\n1. Read the Passion Story of Jesus (Matthew 26–28, Mark 14–16, Luke 22–24, John 18–20).\r\n\r\n2. Thank Jesus for His suffering, His blood, and His love.\r\n\r\n3. Ask the Holy Spirit to reveal the depth of the Cross.\r\n\r\n4. Confess pride, rebellion, self-will, and sin.\r\n\r\n5. Ask Jesus to crucify everything that opposes His will.\r\n\r\n6. Speak the Blood of Jesus over your life, family, and future.\r\n\r\n7. Pray for healing of body, soul, and emotions.\r\n\r\n8. Ask God's Kingdom to reign in your heart, home, and daily life.\r\n\r\n9. Take up your cross and choose obedience.\r\n\r\n10. Stand in faith for freedom, breakthrough, and victory.\r\n\r\n11. Spend time in silence before the Cross.\r\n\r\n12. Listen to what Jesus wants to say to you.\r\n---\r\n\r\n✝️ THE CROSS STORY — JESUS DID THIS FOR YOU\r\n\r\n1. Betrayal\r\nHe was betrayed by a friend.\r\nMatthew 26:14–16\r\n\r\n2. Arrest\r\nHe was arrested though innocent.\r\nMatthew 26:47–56\r\n\r\n3. Trial and Condemnation\r\nHe was falsely accused and condemned.\r\nLuke 23:13–25\r\n\r\n4. Mocking and Beating\r\nHe was mocked, beaten, and scourged.\r\nIsaiah 53:5\r\n\r\n5. Carrying the Cross\r\nHe carried our burden and our judgment.\r\nJohn 19:17\r\n\r\n6. Crucifixion\r\nHe died for our sins.\r\n1 Peter 2:24\r\n\r\n7. Resurrection\r\nHe rose from the dead and lives forever.\r\nMatthew 28:6\r\n\r\n> He suffered. He died. He rose again. He lives!\r\n---\r\n\r\n🙏 PRAYERS OVER THE CROSS — DECLARE THEM\r\n\r\nJesus, thank You for dying on the Cross for my sins.\r\n\r\nI take up my cross and choose to follow You.\r\n\r\nYour blood cleanses me from all sin.\r\n\r\nI speak the Blood of Jesus over my life, family, and home.\r\n\r\nI break every work of darkness in Jesus' name.\r\n\r\nLet the Kingdom of God reign in my life.\r\n\r\nHeal me, restore me, and make me whole.\r\n\r\nI no longer live for myself, but for Christ.\r\n---\r\n\r\n🔥 DEEP TRUTHS ABOUT THE CROSS\r\n\r\nThe Cross is the greatest love ever demonstrated.\r\n\r\nThe Cross is God's highest authority over sin, death, and Satan.\r\n\r\nThe Cross is the government of God established on earth.\r\n\r\nThe Cross is where the old life ends and the new life begins.\r\n\r\nThe Cross is the doorway to heaven.\r\n\r\nThe Cross is the foundation of our freedom.\r\n\r\nThe Cross is the place where justice and mercy meet.\r\n\r\nThe Cross is not weakness—it is the power of God.\r\n---\r\n\r\n👑 TODAY I DECIDE\r\n\r\nI choose the Cross again today.\r\n\r\nI choose obedience over self-will.\r\n\r\nI choose God's Kingdom over my own kingdom.\r\n\r\nI choose Jesus as my King, Lord, and Savior.\r\n\r\nI declare: The Cross is my weapon, my victory, my way, and my future.\r\n---\r\n\r\n✝️ JESUS CHRIST IS LORD\r\n\r\nThe Cross is my life.\r\nThe Cross is my weapon.\r\nThe Cross is my Kingdom.\r\nThe Cross is my way.\r\nThe Cross is my victory.\r\nThe Cross is my future.\r\n\r\n🔥 Jesus Christ is Lord — I belong to Him, today and forever! 🔥",
