  "day35.txt": "DAY 35 – STRATEGIC PRAYER ASSIGNMENT\r\n\r\nJesus Restores What Was Meant for His Service\r\n\r\n> “The thief comes only to steal and kill and destroy; I have come that they may have life, and have it to the full.”\r\nJohn 10:10\r\n\r\n\r\n> “Now to each one the manifestation of the Spirit is given for the common good.”\r\n1 Corinthians 12:7\r\n---\r\n\r\n📖 INTRODUCTION\r\n\r\nToday is not primarily about material possessions.\r\n\r\nToday is about what God has placed within you.\r\n\r\nGod created every believer with gifts, abilities, talents, ministries, and a unique calling.\r\n\r\nThe Holy Spirit gives spiritual gifts not for personal status, but to glorify God, build up His Church, and make His Kingdom visible.\r\n\r\nThat is exactly why the enemy attacks this area so fiercely.\r\n\r\nWhen people never discover their gifts, stop using them, or become discouraged, much of God's purpose remains unfulfilled.\r\n\r\nThe enemy does not merely seek to wound people—he seeks to prevent them from serving.\r\n\r\nHe attacks joy, because joyful believers serve with passion.\r\n\r\nHe attacks peace, because peaceful believers bring hope.\r\n\r\nHe attacks relationships, because we are stronger together.\r\n\r\nHe attacks identity, so people forget who they are in Christ.\r\n\r\nHe attacks time, leaving no room for God's presence.\r\n\r\nHe attacks courage, so no one takes the first step.\r\n\r\nHe attacks love, so people give up.\r\n\r\nHe attacks faith, so no one expects great things from God.\r\n\r\nHe attacks revelation, so believers never discover the gifts the Holy Spirit has entrusted to them.\r\n\r\nToday we are not only praying for restoration.\r\n\r\nWe are praying to become fully equipped and ready again for the work of God's Kingdom.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n👑 1. ASK THE HOLY SPIRIT FOR REVELATION\r\n\r\nPray today:\r\n\r\nLord Jesus, show me everything You originally placed within my life. Reveal the gifts, callings, talents, and opportunities that have been lying dormant because of fear, wounds, disappointment, or discouragement. Open my eyes to see what You see in me.\r\n\r\nAsk yourself:\r\n\r\nWhere did my joy begin to fade?\r\n\r\nWhere did I stop serving?\r\n\r\nWhere did I bury my first dreams?\r\n\r\nWhich gift am I no longer using?\r\n\r\nWhere has fear replaced faith?\r\n\r\nWhere have I become spiritually passive?\r\n\r\nWhere have excuses replaced obedience?\r\n\r\nWhich areas does God want to bring back to life?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🔥 2. IDENTIFY THE ENEMY'S ATTACKS\r\n\r\nAsk God to reveal the areas where discouragement has gained influence.\r\n\r\nPerhaps you struggle with:\r\n\r\nConstant weariness\r\n\r\nHopelessness\r\n\r\nDistraction\r\n\r\nFear\r\n\r\nFeelings of inadequacy\r\n\r\nSelf-doubt\r\n\r\nFear of people\r\n\r\nPast wounds\r\n\r\nUnforgiveness\r\n\r\nFeeling overwhelmed\r\n\r\nComparing yourself to others\r\n\r\nShame\r\n\r\nUnbelief\r\n\r\n\r\nBring each of these areas honestly before Jesus.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n⚔️ 3. PRAY FOR RESTORATION\r\n\r\nLord Jesus,\r\n\r\nRestore my joy.\r\n\r\nIgnite my love for You again.\r\n\r\nRenew my faith.\r\n\r\nStrengthen my courage.\r\n\r\nHeal my heart.\r\n\r\nFill me afresh with Your Holy Spirit.\r\n\r\nTeach me to serve again.\r\n\r\nOpen the doors You have prepared for me.\r\n\r\nShow me my place in Your Kingdom.\r\n\r\nLet my gifts bear lasting fruit.\r\n\r\nMake my life a blessing to others.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🕊️ 4. ACTIVATE YOUR GIFTS\r\n\r\nGifts grow when they are used.\r\n\r\nServe wherever God places you today.\r\n\r\nYour ministry may not begin on a platform.\r\n\r\nIt may begin:\r\n\r\nIn your family\r\n\r\nIn your home\r\n\r\nAt your workplace\r\n\r\nIn your church\r\n\r\nWith a simple prayer\r\n\r\nBy listening to someone\r\n\r\nThrough a word of encouragement\r\n\r\nBy visiting someone\r\n\r\nThrough faithfulness in small things\r\n\r\n\r\nEvery place can become a place of ministry when Christ is at the center.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n📖 5. TODAY'S ASSIGNMENT\r\n\r\nAsk the Holy Spirit to reveal at least five gifts or strengths God has given you.\r\n\r\nWrite them down.\r\n\r\nThen ask:\r\n\r\nHow can I use this gift today?\r\n\r\nWhom can I serve today?\r\n\r\nWhere does God want to use me?\r\n\r\nWhat fear is still holding me back?\r\n\r\n\r\nRead today:\r\n\r\nJohn 10\r\n\r\n1 Corinthians 12\r\n\r\nRomans 12\r\n\r\nEphesians 4\r\n\r\n2 Timothy 1\r\n\r\n\r\nAsk God to renew your mind and equip you afresh for His service.\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n👑 PROCLAMATION\r\n\r\nI am called by God.\r\n\r\nI am equipped by God.\r\n\r\nThe Holy Spirit lives within me.\r\n\r\nMy gifts are given to build up others.\r\n\r\nMy calling belongs to Jesus Christ.\r\n\r\nI choose to be faithful with everything God has entrusted to me.\r\n\r\nMy joy is returning.\r\n\r\nMy courage is returning.\r\n\r\nMy love is returning.\r\n\r\nMy ministry will bear fruit.\r\n\r\nJesus Christ is building His Kingdom, and I have the privilege of serving Him.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🙏 CLOSING PRAYER\r\n\r\nLord Jesus Christ, thank You that You have not only saved me but also called me. Thank You for every gift, every ability, and every opportunity You have entrusted to me. Forgive me for the times I stepped back because of fear, discouragement, or complacency. Restore my joy, strengthen my faith, and teach me to serve You faithfully in everyday life. Let my home, my workplace, my family, and my church become places where Your love is clearly seen. Fill me afresh with Your Holy Spirit and use my life for Your glory. In Jesus' name, Amen.",
